14/02/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government plans to cut youth unemployment by 20 per cent this year, making the issue a focus of its national programme against joblessness, Social Affairs Minister Hristina Hristova said Friday (11 February). 
She added that under the plan, nearly 24,000 jobless Bulgarians up to the age of 29 would find work by the end of the year.
In other news, Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern visited Sofia on Friday and vowed to open an embassy there by year's end. 
He also reiterated Ireland's strong support for Bulgaria's EU membership. 
(Sega - 12/02/05; Bulgarian Government Web site, bTV - 11/02/05)
